Pizza was always good, but they ticked me off last time. So my mother god bless her heart knowing I am a struggling student orders me two pizzas, with a total coming to $30. I use her card as I have done before, and wait. I get a call from the driver saying he is outside and for me to bring my ID and the card used. I explain that my mother ordered the pizza for me and I used her card so I do not have it. I can call her and have her read the number I tell him. He says no it doesn't work like that. So I ask him what do I do and he says call the location. I do that I get a lackluster answer (I wasn't too thrilled either at this point), the guy on the phone says that due to credit card fraud they need to see the ID, but since I order from them a lot and I don't "cause problems" he will tell the driver to give me the food THAT I ORDERED AND THAT WAS PAID FOR ridiculous. I blatantly tell him so someone can't order food for me, and he says no. SMH Okay so let me call the driver back, he decides not to answer, I go outside to find he left. Call the store back to tell them this, he says he'll be back and hangs up on me. About seven mins later I get a call from the driver saying he is outside. He hands me my food silently clearly upset. Why he was upset I'm not sure. I'm the one who had waited at this point almost two hours for food that WAS PAID FOR. I ordered from this place countless times, but apparently their are "pizza thieves" that have ruined their customer service...silliness. Never again.
